Boil a #large pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the spaghetti. Peel and finely
chop the @garlic cloves{2}. Very, very finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{2}.
Chop the @tiger prawns{120%g} into small chunks.

Peel and chop the @vine tomatoes{2} into 2cm cubes.

Cook the @wheat spaghetti{180%g} in the boiling water for ~{11%minutes} or until
'al dente'. When you drain the pasta, keep 3 tbsp of water in case you need to
loosen up the sauce with it.

> Pasta is 'al dente' when cooked through but with a slight hint of firmness left
> in the middle.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #nonstick frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot
add in the garlic and @chilli flakes{1/4%tsp} for ~{30%seconds} (adjust to taste).
Next, add the @chorizo{1}(diced) and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the prawns and
cook for a further ~{2%minutes}.

Add the @tomato passata{1} to the pan and let the mixture bubble away on medium
heat for ~{5-8%minutes}. Add in the chopped tomatoes and cook for another
~{1%minute}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and plenty of @black pepper{}.

> If the sauce is too thick by this point, add 3 tbsp of pasta water to loosen it
> up.

Drain the spaghetti and tip it into the pan. Sprinkle over the parsley and toss
everything together.

Serve into #bowls{} and enjoy!